706811f-a.text:
Smith Street, east side, north from 3rd to 2nd Streets, as seen from
Second Place.
June 5, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

706812f-b.text:
(1)
Smith Street, north from 3rd Street, at the right. At the left, work is in progress on the new Eighth Ave., Subway.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
(2)
The same, showing Smith Street, four years later, after the subway was constructed. It the foreground, right, is Second Street.
June S, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
It's actually a photo of Smith Street and the corner is 2nd Street, I know because the first house going down 2nd Street with a bump out on the façade is still there in 2015.
